programmes.show_description: Two Down, One to Go: The popular 80s sitcom about in-laws forced to share a flat. A frustrated Daphne feels the time is right for some hard bargaining, but will Sam cooperate?
Major Inconvenience: British sitcom about in-laws who are forced to share a flat below their children. Daphne looks forward to finding a kindred spirit in her new neighbour.
Sweet and Sour: The 80s sitcom about the in-laws who share a flat below their children continues. Sam wonders why Daphne and the Major are having an intimate Chinese dinner.
Arrivals and Departures: Michael Elphick and Angela Thorne star in the 80s sitcom. Daphne has a well-heeled visitor from Cheltenham, but discovers they may not have much in common.
Just Desserts: Sitcom about flat-sharing in-laws, whose children have just had their first baby. Sam is envious when Daphne acquires an antique.
